        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 3:23AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 322 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rotan, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stamford, Anson, Hamlin, Rotan, Roby, Lueders, Sylvester, Neinda,
Hobbs, Mccaulley, Paint Creek, Sagerton, Nugent, Avoca, Lake Stamford
Marina, Funston, Hitson, and Tuxedo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
